\title{Definition of Sequent}
\date{2024-02-16}
\author{oscarc}
\taxon{definition}

\p{
    Given a [language](BMT-d001) #{\mathcal{L}}, a \em{sequent} in #{\mathcal{L}} is an ordered pair #{(\Gamma, A)},
    where #{\Gamma} is a set of [#{\mathcal{L}}-sentences](BMT-d013) and #{A} is an [#{\mathcal{L}}-formula](BMT-d009).
    This is usually written #{\Gamma\vdash A}.
}